      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can emails contain colons? This would incorrectly assume a:b@example.com is a valid identity and not attach the prefix. The SearchBuildsRequest would have to explicitly say user:a:b@example.com to search for builds created by a:b@example.com.\n\nCould you combine this with validateCreatedBy in search_builds.go? Then in search internals you can always assume Query.CreatedBy is intended to match Predicate.CreatedBy exactly, and if the identity string isn\u0027t well-formed it just doesn\u0027t match anything in the datastore. I think it might be better not to split the logic up.",
      "revId": "37e59ff37fbae32e99d33966d640b89c9d25491d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
