      "writtenOn": "2020-08-19T18:54:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Only the identity kind, service, allows to have a colon in the value. Unless it explicitly adds the prefix \"service:\" in req, it always regards it as the default kind \"user\". This is how it\u0027s been done in Python. \n\nRE: Could you combine this with validateCreatedBy in search_builds.go?\n\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\nDo you mean directly adding the `user:` prefix for the request.Predicate.CreatedBy in validation if it doest\u0027t specify a identity kind?",
      "parentUuid": "349ce34d_0bf7a026",
      "revId": "37e59ff37fbae32e99d33966d640b89c9d25491d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
